revision.text:
{{documentation subpage}}
{{High-use|114000}}
==Usage==

This maintenance template adds articles to the hidden category [[:Category:{{BASEPAGENAME}}]] to denote articles that have [[Indian English]] spelling, which, as noted in the article, is the same as British English spelling.

Also consider using [[User:फ़िलप्रो/script/EN-IN]].

'''This is not a temporary "cleanup" request template. Therefore, do not remove the template without valid reason, such as a determination the article should use a different language variant.'''

===See also===
{{Use X English}}

<includeonly>{{Sandbox other||
[[Category:Use English templates]]
[[Category:Templates with no visible output]]
}}</includeonly>

== TemplateData ==
{{TemplateDataHeader}}
<templatedata>
{
	"description": "Placed near the top of an article; informs editors to use Indian English in the article.",
	"format": "{{_|_=_}}\n",
	"params": {
		"date": {
			"label": "Month and year",
			"description": "The month and year that the template was placed (in full). \"May 2025\" inserts the current month and year automatically.",
			"type": "line",
			"autovalue": "May 2025",
			"example": "January 2013",
			"suggested": true
		}
	}
}
</templatedata>

